HEADWORD: Atheistical
<hw>A`the*is"tic*al</hw>
<pr>(<?/)</pr>, }</mhw> <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Pertaining to,
implying, or containing, atheism; -- applied to things; <as>as,
<ex>atheistic</ex> doctrines, opinions, or books</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q><qex>Atheistical</qex> explications of natural effects.</q>
<rj><qau>Barrow.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Disbelieving the existence of a God; impious;
godless; -- applied to persons; <as>as, an <ex>atheistic</ex>
writer</as>.</def> -- <wordforms><wf>A`the*is"tic*al*ly</wf>,
<pos>adv.</pos> -- <wf>A`the*is"tic*al*ness</wf>,
<pos>n.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Atheize</ent>⟦br⟧
